metadata.name: A Bugged Forest #80
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. “The Bugged Tree”’s code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations aren’t under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as there’s a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan

metadata.name: Action; System #8
metadata.description:
Action; system is an experimental study inspired by the work of François Morellet. Morellet was one of the founders of the Groupe de Recherche d'Art Visuel (GRAV), founded in the 60s. His work was often informed by systems, a set of rules that determine the artwork, reducing the artist's subjectivity to a minimum.

This work explores what happens when we let go of the strict rule set. Do we ever fully let go?

-----------------
This work was released for the 2023 fundraising exhibition Cure3, and all of the proceeds and 1% of royalties will go to Parkinson's research funds. You can find more information at https://cure3.co.uk/.

-----------------
Controls
- R: new randomized output (the chances of recovering one of these outputs are very slim, that's what the next control is for)
- E: high-res output
- Double click: fullscreen

While you see the eye of Horus, your artwork is loading.

------------------
Made with p5.js & glsl
License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: CHX-1 #170
metadata.description:
Glitching pixels like it’s 1999.

Inspired by 90’s digital aesthetics, CHX-1 takes a random selection of GAN seeds, combines them in unique ways, and processes them –individually and as a group– with a series of glitching dithering algorithms. Generating fun, original, colorful artworks. Millions of possibilities. Have fun!

<<< Base seeds generated offline using personal styleGAN2-ADA models. Image processing and combinations done generatively by the CHX-1 algorithm >>>

GAN –> p5js –> Blockchain


• Artworks can take a few seconds to load when running live code.

• Press “s” (when "open live" is active) to save a PNG image.

metadata.name: ____ - Iteration 2 #50
metadata.description:
This project is part of a larger experiment that explores and celebrates the process of making generative art by progressively releasing iterations, working towards a final release on my main account (tz1RkYY3jr1ocuPdQqrRefr5FqoawKQsmBmD). The iterations will be titled ____ - Iteration 1, ____ - Iteration 2, etc. At this point, the number of iterations has not been determined, but more information will be provided as this experiment unfolds.

The final release will only be made available to those who have collected each iteration (using an allowlist), and will be released for free.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

metadata.name: N E X U S #18
metadata.description:
I present a visual exploration of patterns and colors that relate to each other creating a sense of chaotic harmony. I discover the relationships between them and experiment use noise as a tool, weaving it into a tapestry of unexpected forms that tantalize the senses and inspire the imagination.

___________________

"Nexus" is the connection or link between different things, suggesting a relationship between different elements and a connection between them. 
Work represents the union and connection between all women, and their ability to overcome obstacles and achieve their goals, inviting them to reflect on their role in society and on the importance of their strength and perseverance.

I use this term to connect to all of them through the @GirlsWhoCode foundation.

___________________

20% of primary sales and 10% of secondary sales will be donated to Girls Who Code foundation.

More information can be found at: https://girlswhocode.com/programs/code-at-home

___________________

Made with p5.js

metadata.name: Down the Rabbit Hole #62
metadata.description:
Down the Rabbit Hole is a study in texture and intersecting shapes, inspired by Kandinsky, made with 100% code in p5.js.  I had a lot of fun with the textures.  You might get a 10Print maze as a texture!

Click open and then:
Press 2, 3, 4, or 5 to increase the pixel density.
Press g to add grain.
Press s to save a png.

Resize reverts to pixel density 1.  On a good machine, rendering at density 5 takes 8-10 seconds and adding grain at that density takes another 6 seconds.

I make gen art how-to videos on YouTube.  Come visit me at https://www.youtube.com/c/StevesMakerspace

metadata.name: Semaphore #3
metadata.description:
This piece combines several of my Genuary projects into one for #Genuary32. The main element from the maximalism prompt was based on the idea of semaphore flags, thus prompting the title of this project.

This also contains palettes from movie posters, grids inside grids inside grids, signed distance functions, black and white, and features of p5js I explored on the other days.

The composition of half circles in black and white contrast with recursive grids of rings or full circles of color. 

Press ’s’ to save a PNG of the canvas. You can capture the canvas at any level of texture as you wish.

metadata.name: Aftershock #41
metadata.description:
Turkey was hit by two devastating earthquakes at 6/02/2023 effecting multiple cities.

Aftershock is created to help and support people in earthquake region. 100% of the revenue from primary sales will be send to non governmental organization AHBAP after it's converted to ethereum. All donation will sent from atimtay.eth and will be shared publicly from my twitter account


Artwork info:

Aftershock is based on "Metropolix IX' algorithm. In Metropolis the parameter space was constrained and the cells were painted in a fashion which would create city silhouettes. In Aftershock i removed the constraints and changed the all rulesets and palettes which would give us chaos maybe you can call it a collapsed city.


Features:

6 color palettes and 1 monochrome 
3 subdivison levels 2,3,4 
2 aspect ratios 
10 divison styles 
and some other hidden randomized parameters which doesn't appear on the features but effecting overall outcome

Press 1 to 8 to export PNG at increasing resolution

Murat Atimtay 2023 www.atimtay.xyz
